        var seenCoordinates = [];
        for (var i = 0; i < resources.length; i++) {
            var resource = resources[i];
            // Skips all zero coordinates and AP/EU regions
            if (resource.country_code == 'EU' || resource.country_code == 'AP' || (resource.lat == 0 && resource.lng == 0)) {
                continue;
            }

            if (typeof seenCoordinates[resource.lat + '~' + resource.lng] == 'undefined') {
                var html = generateMapHtml(resource);
                // Add current resource to seen long/lat list
                seenCoordinates[resource.lat + '~' + resource.lng] = {'html': html, 'lat': resource.lat, 'lng': resource.lng, 'location': resource.location, 'type': resource.type};
            } else {
                var html = seenCoordinates[resource.lat + '~' + resource.lng].html + '<hr />' + generateMapHtml(resource);
                seenCoordinates[resource.lat + '~' + resource.lng].html = html;
            }
        }
            
        for(key in seenCoordinates){
            var resource = seenCoordinates[key];

            var image = {
                url: '/assets/icons/' + resource.type + '_marker.png',
                // This marker is 20 pixels wide by 32 pixels high.
                size: new google.maps.Size(24, 24),
                // The origin for this image is (0, 0).
                origin: new google.maps.Point(0, 0),
                // The anchor for this image is the base of the flagpole at (0, 32).
                anchor: new google.maps.Point(12, 24)
            };

            var html = '<div class="map-popup">' + resource.html + '</div>';

            var infowindow = new google.maps.InfoWindow({
                content: html
            });
            var marker = new google.maps.Marker({
                position: {lat: resource.lat, lng: resource.lng},
                map: map,
                icon: image,
                html: html,
                title: resource.name + ' - ' + resource.location,
            });

            // Add the new popup to click
            google.maps.event.addListener(marker, 'click', function() {
                infowindow.setContent(this.html);
                infowindow.open(map, this);
            });

            var point = new google.maps.LatLng(resource.lat, resource.lng);

            bounds.extend(point);
        }

        map.fitBounds(bounds);

        // Limit the zoom level
        google.maps.event.addListener(map, 'zoom_changed', function() {
            if (map.getZoom() > 5) {
                map.setZoom(5);
            } else if (map.getZoom() < 1) {
                map.setZoom(1);
            }
        });
    }

    function generateMapHtml(resource)
    {
        if (resource.type == 'ix') {
            var html = '<img class="map-flag" src="/assets/flags/shiny/24/' + resource.country_code +'.png" title="' + resource.location + '" /> ~ <a href="' + resource.url + '"><strong>' + resource.name + '</strong></a>';
            if (resource.name != resource.description) {
                html += '<br />' + resource.description;
            }
        } else if (resource.type == 'prefix') {
            var html = '<img class="map-flag" src="/assets/flags/shiny/24/' + resource.country_code +'.png" title="' + resource.location + '" /> ~ <a href="' + resource.url + '"><strong>' + resource.prefix + '</strong></a>';
            html += '<br />' + resource.description;
            if (resource.name != resource.description) {
                html += '<br />' + resource.name;
            }
        }

        return html;
    }
</script>
